ctly what BitSight's procurement/legal contracting path and typical cycle time look like once a vendor is chosen."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["SF Executive_Sponsor_Identified__c", "SF OpportunityContactRole", "SF Next_Step__c 6 Jul 2026"], "narrative": "No economic buyer has been identified on this deal at any point in six months (Executive_Sponsor_Identified__c = false, Decision_Maker_Name_Title__c blank). Amy Snider (Global Director of Procurement) has run pricing, demo scheduling, and downselection logistics, but nothing in any call or field shows her controlling budget sign-off. James Hillier is a known BitSight contact at account level but has never appeared on a call or task tied to this opportunity - he is an unconfirmed candidate, not a mapped EB. The new CEO onboarding (Next_Step__c, 6 Jul 2026) now sits squarely on top of this gap: budget authority for the deal may rest with someone Zycus has never met."}, "decision_process": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF Next_Step_History__c (Jan-Jul 2026)", "SF Multiple_approvals__c", "SF Purchase_approvals_Required_from__c"], "narrative": "The call/next-step sequence maps the process clearly: intro (7 Jan) -> scoping + buy-in demo (14/16 Jan) -> vendor pool narrowed to top 5 with prelim pricing (17-23 Feb, Amy attended Zycus's Procurement Pinnacle event 19 Feb) -> shortlisted to 3 finalists with RFP issued (9 Mar, due 20 Mar) -> RFP submitted (18-30 Mar) -> four department demos: Legal (16 Apr), IT (21 Apr), AP/Finance (22 Apr) -> results expected 'this week' as of 4 and 11 May, then the process went silent. No Multiple_approvals__c, Purchase_approvals_Required_from__c, or Does_the_Buyer_need_approval__c data exists, and the new CEO transition (6 Jul) has introduced an unmapped approval layer on top of an already-undocumented chain."}, "decision_criteria": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 14 Jan 2026", "Avoma demo 16 Jan 2026", "SF How_are_you_addressing_your_probl